      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's exactly what the official literature says to make us ignore it. if you look at the way the spaces shift in 'Great Expectations'—it's not just pacing. if you align the gaps as a grid, they actually form a pattern that defies standard typesetting logic. you're a literary expert, you should be able to see the structural anomalies if you stop looking at the words and start looking at the architecture of the page. just look at the spacing patterns in the first chapter of a major Dickens novel and tell me it looks 'natural' to you.",
